description:
This is the first installment of GDG+, a live Google Hangout session with GDG Kuala Lumpur. 

During this 1 hour session, I will share my experience using Google App Engine to build a Facebook Page Tab application for FREE!

Google App Engine gives you the necessary tools & infrastructure complete with SSL support to ensure your Facebook Tab application complies with Facebook's regulations.

This session is meant for beginners and anyone who is just curious :)
title: Using Google App Engine for Facebook Page Tab application.
location: Kuala Lumpur Malaysia

description:
The first meetup of the year! This time, we're bringing +Taylor Ling from AndroidUIUX.com to share his thoughts on what makes a good, well designed Android application. Taylor is well mentioned in +Nick Butcher , +Roman Nurik  &  +Adam Koch show, "Android Design in Action", with his contribution on how to make a better designed Android application.

During this meetup, we will discuss on what, why, when and how to apply best practices in Android design. We will also run through some Malaysian made Android applications to look into room for improvement in terms of UI/UX.

Join us for this meetup and learn how to build a better Android app!

This is a meetup brought to you by the guys from CodeAndroid Malaysia and GDG Kuala Lumpur.
title: Design a Good Looking Android App
location: iTrain Developer Playground

description:
Are you a mobile app developer?
Do you build mobile apps in Android, iOS or HTML5 platform?
Do you face a problem figuring out a solution to build backends for your mobile apps?

You are invited to join us in a session to learn about building scalable mobile application backends using Google Cloud Platform and Google Cloud Endpoints.

What you will learn:
- Build a simple backend API for your mobile app using App Engine.
- Build client libraries for Android, iOS or HTML5.

This meetup will start with a 1 hour talk and a 2 hour codejam.

Let's build something awesome!﻿
title: Accelerate Mobile Development With Google Cloud Endpoints
location: Kuala Lumpur Malaysia

description:
Are you interested in the current trending virtual reality (VR) technology such as Oculus Rift, Samsung Gear VR or Google Cardboard? 

You are invited to join Stanley Phoong and Yap Wen Jiun to start building application for the low cost Google Cardboard using Android API and Unity Game Engine which can be a stepping stone to other more demanding (hardware & software) virtual reality platforms. This session will cover basic understanding of stereoscopic display, OpenGL ES 3D rendering with Android API & Unity Game Engine, input methods such as magnetic switch, gesture input and Bluetooth devices.﻿
title: Develop for Google Cardboard with Android & Unity
location: Level 9, Block E, Megan Avenue 1, Jalan Tun Razak, Kuala Lumpur

description:
A workshop in introducing version control and Git.

Git is a widely-used source code management system for software development. It is a distributed revision control system with an emphasis on speed, data integrity, and support for distributed, non-linear workflows. It is crucial to every programmers, and especially useful for IT students when used with their assignments.

In collaboration with Asia Pacific University Student Developer Society (APUSDS)
